  <brief_title>IMproved PREdiction of Severe Sepsis in the Emergency Department</brief_title>
  <acronym>IMPRESSED</acronym>
  <official_title>Prospective, Non-interventional, Multi-centre Clinical Study to Assess the Clinical Validity of the Heparin Binding Protein (HBP) Assay for Indicating the Presence, or Outcome, of Severe Sepsis (Including Septic Shock), Over 72 Hours, in Patients With Suspected Infection Following Emergency Department Admission.</official_title>
  <sponsors>
